<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-10110] Marshaling using CSV will insert escape char in header if using a pipe as separator</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-10110</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This was an old bug that was supposedly resolved, but with version:2.15.2, the bug remains. The escape characters are still added into the Header Columns when marshaling back the object. &lt;br/&gt;
e.g. &lt;br/&gt;
Separator = \ \ |&lt;br/&gt;
Output: &lt;br/&gt;
Header 1 \ | Header2 \ |...&lt;br/&gt;
Pls. advise when we can expect the fix.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks.&lt;br/&gt;
Reply&lt;/p&gt;</description>
